<headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 27 at 2:03PM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of southeastern Lapeer
County through 245 PM EDT...
At 202 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Dryden, or near Imlay City, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph, pea size hail and very heavy
rainfall.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Dryden around 215 PM EDT.
Imlay City around 230 PM EDT.
Almont around 235 PM EDT.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
